The paper proposes a new randomized algorithm for computing low-rank approximations to matrices, which involves biased sampling and weighted alternating minimization. This algorithm has applications in various areas such as machine learning, data analysis, and scientific computing. The paper also presents two interesting extensions of the algorithm. Given this, the most likely sub-category is cs.NA (Numerical Analysis), followed by cs.LG (Machine Learning), cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms), cs.IT (Information Theory), and cs.SI (Social and Information Networks).
